  "title": "Wit & Whimsy: An Improvised Regency Romance",
  "description": "Do you like your romances written by women? Join us for a completely improvised play inspired by the works of Jane Austen. In each show, our cast creates a brand-new love story—full of longing glances, meddling relatives, brooding suitors, and, of course, the ever-present pressure to secure the most advantageous match.",
  "credits": "<strong>Director</strong>: Delaney Gilmour &amp; Taylor Montalbetti<br><strong>Cast</strong>: Regency Impro Ensemble<br/></br>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "This show is an improvised play inspired by the books of Jane Austen. Each performance tells a new love story made up on the spot. You will see characters fall in love, deal with family drama, and try to find the best possible match. The cast uses humour, drama, and romance to bring this world to life.",
